<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Banks Merger Leads to Political Crisis in Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian President Nachagyn
Bagabandy said Thursday the government's decision to merge the
state-owned Restoration Bank into the private Golomt Bank was
illegal and should be cancelled.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the Great Hural, or parliament, Bagabandy called
on the legislature to annul the government decision and regulate
on the banks' lendings and borrowings of money.
</P>
<P>
Public disappointment and distrust of the government has been
growing and society would descend into turmoil if the government
lost the people's support, the president said.
</P>
<P>
The government adopted the secret merger decision on May 27
without parliamentary debate, and was met with strong opposition
from the Mongolian People's Revolution Party (MPRP), which called
the move a misappropriation of national assets by a few people in
power.
</P>
<P>
The MPRP decided to abstain from parliamentary sessions unless
the government decision was cancelled.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, it threatens to call for dissolving the Great Hural
if its demand is not met.
</P>
<P>
The Great Hural is scheduled to further discuss the issue on
Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
