- - - -
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- The Albanian government protested on Wednesday
against an alleged Yugoslavian military violation of the border
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the Albanian Telegraphic Agency, Yugoslavian
frontier guards shot dead an Albanian who was on Albanian
territory on Tuesday, then crossed the border to pull the body
across to Yugoslavian soil.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to Belgrade's charge d'affaires ad interim to
Tirana, the Albanian Foreign Ministry warned that the dangerous
incident constituted an escalation of the Kosovo crisis.
(Albania-Yugoslavia-Dispute)
