vowed to step up efforts to resolve the bad-loan problem of
Japanese banks so as to stimulate the domestic economy and restore
market confidence.
</P>
<P>
"To spark a rebound in the stalled economy, I will do my best
to help write off bad loans, achieve growth driven by domestic
demand, open Japanese markets further and promote deregulation,"
Hashimoto said at the end of the regular 158-day Diet (parliament)
session. (Japan-Economy-Hashimoto) 
</P>
