<HEADLINE> Meeting to Promote African Development Begins in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Tokyo international conference
on African development (TICAD ii) starts a two-day second
preparatory meeting here Friday to deliberate on agenda for
action to promote development of the continent.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations information center said in a statement to
the Zimbabwe News Agency Thursday that 24 members of the
preparatory committee were expected to attend the meeting which
is organized by the United Nations, Japan and the Global
Coalition for Africa.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is one of three such meetings set to prepare an
''agenda for action'' for African development with specific steps
to be taken by African countries and their development partners
in social development.
</P>
<P>
The committees also promote industrial and agricultural
development among other issues.
</P>
<P>
TICAD ii will be held in Tokyo, Japan in October and is aimed
at furthering African development through the ''agenda for
action''.
</P>
<P>
''The main message of this agenda for action for African
development is poverty alleviation through accelerated and
sustainable economic growth and further integration of African
economies into the global economy,'' said the statement.
</P>
<P>
TICAD promotes south-south cooperation with a focus on the
ownership of African development based on national development
priorities to be supported by the international community.
</P>
<P>
The first TICAD was held in Tokyo in 1993 after which a
declaration on African development was adopted, reaffirming
partnership with shared responsibilities based on the principle
of self-reliance of African countries and the commitment of the
international community to support these efforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
