<HEADLINE> Plane Crash Kills 11 in Montreal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A small commuter plane exploded on
emergency landing near Montreal Thursday, killing all 11 people on
board.
</P>
<P>
The twin-engine turboprop was engulfed in flames as it made a
desperate attempt to land at Mirable airport.
</P>
<P>
Though the pilot did succeed on landing the plane, the aircraft
exploded and veered off the runway, media reports said.
</P>
<P>
The emergency vehicles put out the fire as quickly as possible,
but there was no survivors. All 11 people on board, including two
crew, were killed.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien said he was shocked and
saddened to learn of the terrible incident at Mirable.  
</P>
