<HEADLINE> Investment Activities Increase in Ethiopia's Dire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Investors with an aggregate
capital of over 143 million U.S. Dollars have been licensed over
the past 10 months in Dire Dawa, the second largest city in
Ethiopia, to engage in various development sectors.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency Thursday quoted the Dire Dawa
investment office as saying that the investment activities in the
city this fiscal year is equivalent to what has been done over
the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The office said most of the 72 investment projects focus on
agriculture and agro-industry.
</P>
<P>
The office attributed the increase of investment activities in
the city to the decisions of grant land at reasonable price and
at times for free in addition to other incentives the city
administration extended to investors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
