<HEADLINE> Zanzibar Fights Drugs Offences </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Zanzibar government has
tried every means to strike on drug offences and arrested 122
suspects including two women in 1997, a report reaching here said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chief Minister Mohamed Bilal told the Zanzibar House of
Representatives Wednesday evening though the isles saw a slight
decline in the number of arrests last year, the government will
go further by using sniffer dogs, sophisticated instrument to
detect hidden drugs.
</P>
<P>
"A British expert will provide training for port officials,
the police and cargo inspection staff on better methods of
uncovering concealed drugs," he said.
</P>
<P>
The government also sensitized the public to the hazard of
the drug abuse by the youth mostly aged between 15 and 35 who
usually contract tuberculosis, skin diseases and malnutrition,
said the minister.
</P>
<P>
"Three habitual drug users have been completely reformed while
18 others are well on their way to follow suit," he said, adding
that the social resources have been mobilized for the renovation
of a special clinic for treating more drug abusers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
