<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, June 19 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Eight Turkish soldiers and civil guards have been
killed in an attack launched by the rebels of the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) in southeastern Turkey, the semi-official
Anatolia News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the PKK militants late Thursday night
shot dead one officer, four soldiers and three village guards in
the attack against the Yufkali village near the town Semdinli in
Hakkari Province bordering Iran.
</P>
<P>
The PKK rebels escaped from the scene soon after their attack
in the region, added the agency. (Turkey-PKK-Killing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Syrian President Hafez al-Assad is to pay his first
visit in more than 20 years to Lebanon this fall, notably to
climax Damascus' official recognition of Lebanon's statehood and
independence.
</P>
<P>
The Orient radio Friday quoted Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik
Hariri, who is visiting the United States, as saying Assad "will
visit us at the invitation of President Elias Hrawi before
October." (Lebanon-Syria-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on Friday said he
would not seek a third term in office in 2000 when the next
presidential elections are held.
</P>
<P>
On a short visit to Kostroma region northeast of Moscow,
Yeltsin told students of the Kostroma Agricultural Academy that he
would not run for a third term.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin, who is serving his second term, has repeatedly fudged
on the issue over the last few months, sometimes leaving doubts on
whether he would run, then ruling out a third term.
(Russia-Yeltsin)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- The U.S. dollar fell below 135 yen in Tokyo Friday for
the first time in a month on expectations of yen-supportive news
from an international meeting to be held here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The dollar was quoted at 134.97-135.00 yen at 5 p.m. (local
time), down from 137.30-33 yen at 9 a.m., and 137.80-90 yen late
Thursday in New York. (Japan-Foreign-Exchange) 
</P>
</TEXT>
