<HEADLINE> German Parliament Renews Peace Mission in Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The German parliament overwhelmingly
approved on Friday the extension of the German peacekeeping
mission in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
The mission, which will expire on Friday, is part of the
NATO-led Stabilization Force (SFOR) in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Since there is no specific timing for the NATO force to
withdraw from Bosnia, the German parliament did not set a time
limit for the the German contingent. But it decided to review its
operation every half a year.
</P>
<P>
The German parliament also decided that the German contingent
would remain at the current level of 3,000 soldiers.
</P>
<P>
German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel told the parliament
earlier that the continued presence of peacekeeping troops in
Bosnia was necessary because the fragile peace there had to be
safeguarded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
