<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Istanbul Stock Exchange Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's Istanbul Stock Exchange
National-100 Index closed at 4,007.11 points on Friday, up 41.6
points, or 1.05 percent, from that on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover stood at over 81 trillion Turkish liras (over 308
million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980619.0046 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Africa in Danger of Being Marginalized: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Deputy Foreign Minister
Nicholas Goche warned Friday that Africa is in real danger of
remaining largely marginalized from the global economy.
</P>
<P>
He said globalization was a reality which had brought changes
to the world economy but Africa's share of that global economy
had not yet improved.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking at the opening ceremony of a two-day second
preparatory meeting of the Tokyo International Conference on
African Development (TICAD) which started here Friday.
</P>
<P>
''In 1992, for instance, the total value of Africa's exports
was only two percent of the world total compared to 17 percent
for Asia and the Pacific, four percent for Latin America and the
Caribbean, 10 percent for Japan and 15 percent for North
America,'' Goche said.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the preparatory meeting, being attended by
representatives from 11 African countries, two Asian countries,
five donor countries and 10 non-governmental organizations, would
examine trade issues with a view to resolving capacity
constraints and other problems hindering Africa's participation
in the global economy.
</P>
<P>
TICAD is a forum aimed at furthering African development
through an ''agenda for action'' and promoting South-South
cooperation with a focus on the development of Africa based on
national priorities to be supported by the international
community.
</P>
<P>
Goche added despite multiple initiatives to address the issue
of debt, the problem still remained a major constraint to
sustained growth and development in Africa.
</P>
<P>
''This forum brings together creditor and debtor nations. The
issue of external debt has been on the agenda since the early
eighties when the debt crisis first surfaced,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
The deputy minister also said that ''the outcome of our
deliberations here will have a significant impact on the shape
and content of the agenda for action to be adopted in Tokyo.''
</P>
<P>
TICAD is a Japanese initiative designed to support African
efforts at economic recovery and development.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will prepare the draft agenda for action to be
adopted at TICAD II to be held in October in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
It will focus on issues related to social development which
include poverty alleviation, education, health, population,
private sector-led development, agriculture and environment, good
governance, conflict resolution and external debt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
