<HEADLINE> Chinese Party Leader On Role of Youth In Country's Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Vice-president Hu Jintao said here
today that the future of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
depends on whether it can win over the country's 320 million young
people, calling them a major force in promoting historical
development and social progress.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Standing Committee of the CPC Central
Committee, was addressing the opening ceremony of the 14th National
Congress of the Chinese Communist Youth League, the world's
largest youth organization, which has 68.5 million members between
the ages of 14 and 28.
</P>
<P>
Hu, emphasized the importance the Party places on the Congress,
and pointed out that the Standing Committee of the CPC Central
Committee's Political Bureau, the Party's leaders, were present at
the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
These included President Jiang Zemin, who is General Secretary
of the Party, and Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Wei Jianxing
and Li Lanqing.
</P>
<P>
"The 14th National Congress of the Chinese Communist Youth
League is a significant meeting being held at the turn of the
century and at a crucial moment in China's reforms, opening-up,
and modernization," Hu told the more than 1,400 delegates.
</P>
<P>
He said that there has been great progress in China's youth
movement of the 20th century and that it has proven that it was
only with the CPC's leadership that Chinese youth could achieve
the things they did.
</P>
<P>
The new century is filled with opportunities and challenges, he
said, and the Party hopes that the country's younger generation
can live up to its expectations and those of the people, and
contribute to the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
