<HEADLINE> Chinese Official On Using Deng's Theory For Overseas Chinese Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Vice-premier Qian Qichen told a
seminar on Deng Xiaoping's Theory and overseas Chinese affairs
here today that China will use it to do a better job in the work
on overseas Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Deng upheld the policies for overseas Chinese of Chairman Mao
Zedong and Premier Zhou Enlai, which emphazised protecting the
rights of overseas Chinese and overseas Chinese who have returned,
Qian said.
</P>
<P>
Deng also regarded a proper handling of overseas Chinese
affairs an indispensable part of China's opening up strategy and
an important way to form friendship with other nations and people,
Qian said.
</P>
<P>
He reviewed China's progress in this area and pointed out that
the effectiveness of Deng's theory on handling overseas Chinese
affairs have been proven as most overseas Chinese and returned
Chinese have contributed to China's modernization drive and the
reunification of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
As China continues with its opening up and modernization,
overseas Chinese will have an even bigger role to play, Qian
concluded. 
