Ung Huot said he and Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van Khai
were very optimistic that the border issues could be resolved by
the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
They also decided that the next discussions of border issues
between the two countries would be held in Hanoi in late August,
after the general elections of Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
The two parties would sign a memorandum on Saturday concerning
the border talks. 
</P>
