<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Mozambique Renew Medical Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June (Xinhua) -- The governments of China and
Mozambique signed an agreement on medical cooperation between the
two countries here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Under the renewed pact, China will send its 12th medical team
to Mozambique to help the local people in the near future this
year.
</P>
<P>
The doctors of the Chinese medical team will increase from 12
to 16. Among them, twelve will work in the Maputo Central
Hospital, the biggest and best in this southern African country.
The other four doctors will work in a district hospital in
Maputo, a source in the Chinese embassy here told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Besides specialists in surgery, acupuncture, anaesthesia,
otolarygology and orthopaedics, China will add experts in the
fields of gynaecology and orthopaedic surgery to the new team, to
cater for the needs of the Mozambican people.
</P>
<P>
China began sending a medical team to Mozambique, a former
Portugese colony in 1976, only one year after its independence,
and the team is being replaced every two years.
</P>
<P>
So far, 11 batches of Chinese doctors have been sent to help
the Mozambicans. And the incumbent team will return to China in
August when its terms expire.
</P>
<P>
For over 20 years of the medical cooperation, nearly one
million Mozambican people have been cured by the Chinese doctors,
whose consummate medical skills and noble ethics have won praises
from the Mozambicans, statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Mozambican Deputy Minister of Health Abdul Noormahamedi and
China's Ambassador to Mozambique Shao Guanfu signed the pact here
on behalf of their respective countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the signing ceremony, Noormahamedi said with the
situation in Mozambique becoming more stable and its economy
growing steadily, his government hopes that China would invest
more in the health field of Mozambique and other sectors.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Shao promised that China plans to strengthen the
cooperation between the two countries in making medicines from
Chinese herbs and in the field of pharmaceutics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
