<HEADLINE> Chinese CPPCC Standing Committee Second Meeting Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The second Meeting of the Standing
Committee of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), whose main topic of
discussion was the strategy of improving the country with science
and technology, ended here today.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China Central Committee and
Chairman of the National Committee of the CPPCC, presided over the
closing ceremony this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Song Jian, a vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
CPPCC, who spoke at the meeting, said that China has acted in time
with its strategy of improving the country with science and
technology and that other countries are developing a
knowledge-based economy.
</P>
<P>
China should improve its science and technology in agriculture
and combine it with the economy, he said, and develop hi-tech
industries, increase infrastructure research, develop education,
and increase financial input in education.
</P>
<P>
The nation also needs to increase awareness of the important
role of science and education in social development, he said.
</P>
<P>
The third meeting of the Standing Committee of the National
Committee of CPPCC is expected to be held in Beijing in October,
with agriculture and rural development as its main areas of
discussion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
