<HEADLINE> A Quiet Week for Cyprus Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Market has
experienced a relatively quiet week as the market consolidated at
the current price levels.
</P>
<P>
According to the weekly market review issued Friday by the
Cyprus Investment and Securities Corporation Limited (CISCO), the
CISCO All-Share Index closed at 431.9 points on Thursday,
a drop of 0.8 point over the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The only session that ended with gains was last Friday, when
the market climbed 4.9 points to 437.7 points. But the gain was
reversed gradually in the next four trading days.
</P>
<P>
Monday witnessed the biggest decline in the week, as the market
fell 2.8 points to close at 434.9 points. This decline was
triggered by the speculation that France would propose delaying
the Cyprus accession talks with the European Union (EU) at the EU
summit held the same day in Britain's Welsh capital Cardiff.
</P>
<P>
The market continued sliding in the following days within a
marginal range between 0.7 to 1.6 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of transactions in the week rose to 5.2
million Cyprus pounds (about 10.4 million U.S. dollars), from
4.1 million pounds (about 8.2 million dollars) in the previous
week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
