<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Vice-minister of Public Security
Bai Jingfu has asked Macao police to get tougher on crime to
better protect public security.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with the head of Macao's police, Antonao Francisco
Marques Batpasta, here today, Bai said there are only about 500
days left until Dec. 20, 1999 when Macao returns to China. But the
public security situation there has not been as good as it could
be in recent months and that the Macao government should see that
Macao has better public order before that date.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes that Macao's police could play a more
active role in guaranteeing the smooth transition by acting
promptly to stem the increase in crime. Police in the inland areas
is ready to increase cooperation with the Macao police in stopping
cross-border crime, Bai said.
</P>
<P>
The Macao police chief said that they would work harder to
fight crime and ensure Macao's smooth transition.
