<HEADLINE> Nepali King Speaks Highly of Nepal-China Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Nepali King Birendra said here
Friday that the Nepali-Chinese relations, marked as they are by
"goodwill, mutual trust and understanding," have been developing
in a spirit of true friendship and good neighborliness.
</P>
<P>
Birendra made these remarks when accepting the letter of
credence presented by Zeng Xuyong, China's new ambassador to
Nepal, at the Royal Palace.
</P>
<P>
"The close and cordial bonds between our two countries have
been further consolidated by exchange of visits at various levels
over the years," said the king.
</P>
<P>
He recalled with pleasure the state visit to Nepal by Chinese
President Jiang Zemin in 1996 and his own visit to China the same
year.
</P>
<P>
"It is a matter of satisfaction that China has for over four
decades been an active partner in our development efforts with its
involvement in major sectors of the Nepalese economy," the king
said.
</P>
<P>
"Nepal and China, guided by the Five Principles of Peaceful
Co-existence, share many things in pursuance of their foreign
policies," he said. "We wish to see continuation of closer
interaction between our two countries in the coming years."
</P>
<P>
Zeng said that there are no unsettled issues between China and
Nepal, and over the years, the two countries have carried out
fruitful cooperation in many fields and there have been frequent
exchanges of high-level visits between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
He said that when visiting Nepal at the end of 1996, President
Jiang Zemin agreed with King Birendra on establishing between the
two countries a good-neighborly partnership of lasting friendship
oriented towards the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"During my tenure of office, I will exert my efforts and make
my due contribution to the steady development and consolidation of
the friendly relations and cooperation between China and Nepal and
the traditional friendship between our two peoples," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zeng arrived in Kathmandu on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
