<HEADLINE> Germany Sees Strong Growth in New Car Registrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- New car registrations in Germany
soared in the first five months of this year, coming close to the
peaks registered in the early years after German reunification in
1990, official figures showed Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the German Federal Vehicles Office, Germany's
total car registrations reached 1.9 million in the period from
January to May, up 4.8 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The figure fell just short of the 2.2 million registered in the
same period in 1991 and 2.1 million in 1992, when a car boom was
triggered by the reunification.
</P>
<P>
In May, Germany's new car registrations totalled 385,249, up
7.7 percent from the level of a year ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
