<HEADLINE> Asia-Pacific Water Polo Tourney to Open in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The inaugural Asia-Pacific Water
Polo International Invitational Tournament has attracted a field
of six teams, the organizers announced here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the two-day event starting this weekend will
be teams from Guangzhou of China's mainland, Guam, Malaysia,
Chinese Taipei, India and hosts the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
The teams will be pooled into two groups of three, with
Guangzhou, Guam and Malaysia in Group A and Group B consisting of
Chinese Taipei, India and Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
Group A teams will play their Group B counterparts on Sunday,
according to their respective rankings decided on their
performance in the single round-robin group competitions on
Saturday, to decide the final placings.
</P>
<P>
The inaugural tournament was organized by the Hong Kong Amateur
Swimming Association (HKASA) and the Provisional Urban Council.
India has offered to host the second annual tournament next year,
with details to be decided and announced later this year,
according to a HKASA spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
