<HEADLINE> Share Prices Mixed On Shanghai Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 19 (Xinhua)-- Share prices on the Shanghai Stock
Exchange have been rising since Thursday, with the Composite Stock
Index finishing at 1,392.88 points today, up 0.6 percent over last
week, because of the Japan-U.S. foreign exchange actions.
</P>
<P>
The SSR-300 Index, based on 30 blue chips selected from more
than 400 A-shares on the Shanghai Stock Exchange, were down 3.69
points on a weekly basis, closing at 3540.11 points.
</P>
<P>
Total transaction this week was 26.568 billion yuan, down 7.1
percent from last week, with 258 of the Exchange's 453 shares
gaining in price and 182 down.
</P>
<P>
B-shares (for overseas investors) closed at 43.55 points, an
increase of 4.56 percent over last week. Prices of 38 of the 51
B-shares were up.
</P>
<P>
Trading in funds was light this week, with a total of 1.98
billion yuan, or 10 percent more than last week.
</P>
<P>
Bond trading was rather active, climbing 30 percent to 59.37
billion yuan. 
</P>
