<HEADLINE> Northeast China City to Offer 143 Projects for Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Tonghua, a city in northeast
China's Jilin Province, will hold a trade bidding fair June 23-25,
and will list 143 projects for investment.
</P>
<P>
Situated in the Changbai Mountain area, Tonghua is abundant in
natural resources. The city has formed three pillar
industries: medicine, food and building materials. In 1997,
Tonghua earned more than 570 million yuan in profits from the
medicine industry alone.
</P>
<P>
An official with the city government said that Tonghua will
help investors get high returns with a favorable environment,
preferential policies and cooperative partners.
</P>
<P>
He also disclosed that about 46 state-owned enterprises will
sell their property rights in such fields as machinery processing,
building materials and textiles involving more than 500 million
yuan and nearly one million square meters of land.
</P>
<P>
Tonghua will also list 70 projects to attract foreign
investment in fields such as medicine, chemicals and building
materials in the form of joint venture, cooperatives, compensation
trade, and leasing. 
</P>
