<HEADLINE> Anhui Farmers Enjoy Improved Living Standard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in east China's Anhui
Province have enjoyed a general improvement in living standards in
recent years, according to a recent survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey conducted by the Anhui Province Rural Economic
Survey Team showed that the per capita income for farmers has
grown by an average 8.6 percent annually over the past two
decades.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the per capita income of Anhui farmers increased to
1,808 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The increase in income was attributed to the diversification of
economic activities of Anhui farmers to supplement their earnings
from farming.
</P>
<P>
Anhui Farmers have enjoyed constantly improving housing
quality, with the 1997 per capita floor space standing at 20.05
sq.m., compared to only 8.46 sq. m. in 1978.
</P>
<P>
Average consumption expenditures in 1997 stood at 1,336.6
yuan, with 309 yuan for non-staple foods.
</P>
<P>
The survey also revealed that average entertainment
expenditures jumped from a mere 1.99 yuan to 189.21 yuan between
1978-1997, with per capita expenditures on clothing rising from
10.17 yuan to 86.94 yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
