<DOCNO> XIE19980619.0111 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Bank Increases Loan Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) - The Agricultural Bank of China
(ABC), one of the country's big four commercial banks, has
accelerated the extension of loans this year to help boost
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The bank issued 32.5 billion yuan in loans in the first five
months, including 9.4 billion yuan in May, according to official
statistics.
</P>
<P>
A bank official said that ABC will continue to give lending
priority to the agricultural sector this year. He added that the
bank has budgeted its loans for the agricultural sector at 35
billion yuan, 1.1 billion yuan more than last year, or more than
20 percent of the bank's loan portfolio this year, which is valued
at 160 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The bank also increased lending to the real estate sector,
mainly targeting residential housing and the renovation of rundown
buildings. It is also seeking to start new forms of loan services
to finance home buyers.
</P>
<P>
ABC also beefed up financial support for infrastructure
projects and basic industries, including transportation,
telecommunications, power and high-technology, in the first five
months. The bank plans to extend 15 billion yuan in fixed-asset
loans this year, a surge of 12 billion yuan from last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the bank also attached great importance to meeting
the financial needs of medium- and small-size enterprises,
joint-stock companies, overseas-funded enterprises and private
businesses. Its planned loans for rural and township enterprises,
for example, will reach 25 billion yuan this year, 5 billion yuan
more than in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
