<HEADLINE> Share Prices Dip on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Share prices dipped slightly on
the Singapore market Friday after a two-day continuos rise as the
benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index (STII) lost 10.48 points
to close at 1,122.91 points.
</P>
<P>
Share prices were lower on the whole day but off their lows
following some firming in regional currencies in the late
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Trading was relatively quiet with most investors taking a
cautious wait-and-see stance ahead of the G-7 (Group of Seven)
meeting of senior finance officials in Japan on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The wider market was weaker with many blue chips coming under
profit-taking after a strong mid-week rally.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume dropped to 146.88 million units, valued
at 321.25 million Singapore dollars (194.70 million U.S. dollars).
Falls led rises by 203 to 83 while 301 other counters remained
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
DBS Land remained the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 20.99 million units. It was followed by
Wing T which had 8.235 million shares traded. Easyknit Thk was
next with 7.10 million shares changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Rothmans topped the gainers of the day as it rose by 40 cents
to finish at 10.90 Singapore dollars. DBS and DBS F increased by
20 cents respectively. The former closed at 7.50 Singapore dollars
while the latter ended at 10.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 1.60 Singapore dollars to end at 19.30 Singapore
dollars. SIA F lost 80 cents to close at 8.70 Singapore dollars.
Asean was next which fell by 40 cents to finish at 5.10 U.S.
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
