<HEADLINE> CPPCC Members Suggest Legal Backing for High-Tech Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- China's CPPCC members today
suggested the government offer legal backing for the
development of the country's high-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came at the third plenary meeting of the second
meeting of the Standing Committee of the Ninth National Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
that was held here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Participants indicated that high-tech competition has become
the focus in the international community, and accelerating the
development of high-tech industry is related to the fate
of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Gong Shiping, a member of the Standing Committee of the CPPCC
National Committee and vice-chairman of the Liaoning Provincial
Committee of the CPPCC, suggested the government spend 1.5 percent
of the gross domestic product on social research and development
each year, and fix the allocation in the form of a law.
</P>
<P>
Wu Wenying, alaos a member of the Standing Committee of the
CPPCC National Committee, said the government should take
effective measures to fight against unfair competition hindering
the commercialization and industrialization of scientific
research achievements.
</P>
<P>
She said a law governing the high-tech development zone was
submitted to the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress last year and was suggested for approval this year to
regulate the development of the country's high-tech zones.
</P>
<P>
Other members of the Standing Committee of the CPPCC National
Committee also suggested the government stipulate measures in
government purchases, personnel, finance and tax collection to
support the development of the high-tech industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
