<HEADLINE> Drought Eases in Heilongjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The drought has eased in northeast
China's Heilongjiang Province, a major autumn grain producer in
the country, because of the local government's efforts to fight
the disaster.
</P>
<P>
Nearly one-half of the province suffered from drought during
this year's spring planting, while more than four million hectares
of cultivated land was in the most serious condition.
</P>
<P>
To fight against drought, the province invested 543 million
yuan and dug 60,000 new wells to ensure irrigation for 2.4 million
hectares of arable land.
</P>
<P>
The rainfall in April also helped farmers, according to the
local government.
</P>
<P>
This year, the province planted eight million hectares of
crops, up 80,000 hectares from last year. It also invested 14.2
billion yuan in buying fertilizer and farm machinery for the
spring sowing, laying a strong foundation for this year's good
harvest.
</P>
<P>
The province yielded 31 billion kilograms of grain last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
