<HEADLINE> Beijing Launches Help-the-elderly Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 enterprises and
government institutions in the Chinese capital have jointly
launched a program to help the city's elderly.
</P>
<P>
They have issued a special card that allows local elderly
people preferential treatment in handling household chores,
catering, recreation, travel and shopping as well as many social
services.
</P>
<P>
Part of the program includes the construction of an apartment
building for the elderly covering more than 3,000 square
meters. The project, located near the Fragrant Hills in western
Beijing, is expected to be completed within the year.
</P>
<P>
At present, Beijing's population aged 60 and older is 1.6
million, or 13 percent of the city's total. That of the country
stands at 120 million and is expected to reach 130 million by
2000, or 10 percent of the country's total population. 
</P>
