<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S.Korea Accepts DPRK's Invitation to Unification Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 19 (Xinhua) -- South Korea Friday accepted
invitation from the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
to attend a "grand festival for national reconciliation, unity and
unification" scheduled for August 14-15 in the truce village of
Panmunjom.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time South Korea has accepted such an
invitation.
</P>
<P>
"We will make a proposal next week to North Korea for a
working-level meeting to discuss how the festival should be
arranged," South Korean Unification Minister Kang In-duk said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
On June 10, in letters to South Korean President Kim Dae-jung
and overseas Koreans, the DPRK invited them to attend the festival
marking the 53rd anniversary of Korea's independence from Japan on
August 15, 1945.
</P>
<P>
"North Korea has formed a preparatory committee for the
festival, and we are to form a same committee comprising of
members from political parties and social organizations," Kang
said.
</P>
<P>
South Korea rejected previous DPRK proposals on the ground that
they were attached with preconditions, including South Korea
repealing its security law and abolishing its intelligence agency.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK did not mention the preconditions this time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
