<HEADLINE> Customs Office Opens in Chongqing Economic Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A Customs Office began
operations today in the economic and technology development zone
in Chongqing Municipality.
</P>
<P>
With an urban and rural population of more than 30 million,
Chongqing was separated from Sichuan Province to become China's
fourth municipality under the direct administration of the central
government in March of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The development zone in Chongqing is the only national-level
economic zone in southwest China. The opening of the Customs
facility is expected to make the zone more attractive to investors
and to facilitate the handling of foreign trade for the
municipality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
