<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Friday.
</P>
<P>
Profit taking and weaknesses in regional stock markets
continued to pull values lower.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index stood at
467.61, down 4.21 points, the all-share Emas Index fell 1.11
points to 119.7 and the Industrial Index shed 11.29 points to
909.51 while the Second Board lost 1.07 points to 103.63.
</P>
<P>
Losers led advancers 382 to 141 with 148 counters unchanged and
268 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was thin at 112.684 million shares valued at
237.469 million ringgit (about 60.578 million U.S. dollars)
against Thursday's 210.331 million shares worth 470.541 million
ringgit (about 120.035 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board volume fell to 108.738 million shares worth
231.457 million ringgit (about 59.045 million dollars) from 201.78
million valued at 456.337 million ringgit (about 116.412 million
dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover decreased to 3.946 million shares
valued at 6.012 million ringgit (about 1.533 million dollars) from
Thursday's 8.551 million shares worth 14.204 million ringgit
(about 3.623 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals declined sharply to 1.173 million shares
valued at 3.888 million ringgit (about 992,000 dollars) from 26.34
million shares worth 60.859 million ringgit (about 15.525 million
dollars) on Thursday. 
</P>
