<HEADLINE> Sacramento Guard Abdul-Rauf Heads for Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Sacramento Kings guard Mahmoud
Abdul-Rauf will leave the National Basketball Association club to
continue his career in Turkey.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Sacramento, Formerly known as Chris
Jackson, Abdul-Rauf changed his name two years after embracing the
Islamic religion in 1991. His five-year contract expires on
July 1.
</P>
<P>
Abdul-Rauf played through an injury-plagued eighth season in
the league, his second with Sacramento after being acquired from
the Denver Nuggets. He played in only 31 games, recording career
lows in points (7.3), rebounds (1.2) and assists (1.9).
</P>
<P>
Abdul-Rauf spent the last three months of the season on the
injured list due to the flu and a career-threatening corneal
ulcer in his left eye. The eye improved last month but could
return. 
</P>
