<HEADLINE> Nepal's GDP to Grow by 2.07 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The gross domestic product (GDP)
of Nepal is estimated to grow by 2.07 percent during the current
fiscal year which ends in mid-July, the Kantipur daily reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The GDP in the first 10 months of the current fiscal year
amounted to 293.46 billion rupees (about 4.5 billion U.S.
dollars), the Nepali-language paper said, quoting a report by the
Central Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural sector accounted for 39.13 percent of the GDP
while other sectors contributed 60.87 percent, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the agricultural sector witnessed a growth of 1.1
percent and other sectors increased by 2.78 percent in the GDP.
</P>
