<HEADLINE> 18 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces killed 18
rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in military
operations in southeastern Turkey, an official statement said on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that the security forces had clashed with the PKK
militants at Yassidag region in Eruh town of Siirt province and 18
PKK rebels were killed in the conflicts.
</P>
<P>
However, the statement failed to disclose when the clashes
broke out in the region.
</P>
<P>
It added that the security forces captured three PKK
guerrillas in the operations at Cirpili village of Eruh town.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 14-year-old separatist war in
eastern and southeastern Turkey, which has claimed over 35,000
lives since August 1984. 
</P>
