<HEADLINE> East China Province Battling Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 19 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province is
battling against an expanding flood caused by about week-long heavy
rains.
</P>
<P>
River banks have been breached in Qianshan, Yiyang, Yugan and
Yujiang counties in the northeast part of the province.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang, Ganjiang and other branches of the Yangtze as well as
Boyang Lake are experiencing rising water levels. More rains could
worsen the problem, according to weather forecasts.
</P>
<P>
Affected regions are mobilizing their resources to control the
floods and engage in rescue work.
</P>
<P>
