<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Budget for Next Fiscal Year Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania's parliament has
endorsed the 1998/99 budget, which means the government is
allowed to spend 1,007,786 million Shillings (about 1.52 billion
U.S. Dollars) in the next fiscal year from July to next June.
</P>
<P>
The budget was approved in Dodoma Thursday after 153 members
of parliament cast ballots in favor while 113 others were absent
from voting, media reports said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Presenting the budget plans for the 1998/99 fiscal year at the
National Assembly last week, the finance minister Daniel Yona
said the government plans to collect 695,165.9 million Shillings
from its domestic sources while spend 1,007,786 million
Shillings.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will cover the budget deficit from
domestic sources, external assistance and various revenue
measures. 
</P>
