<HEADLINE> Yaxing-Benz Begins Mass Production of Luxury Buses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A state-of-the-art production line
for luxury buses was put into production in Yaxing-Benz Ltd,
China's largest bus manufacturer, here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The event marks the production of the first domestically
manufactured luxury buses reaching advanced international
standards, according to Ju Baocai, general manager of the
Sino-Germany joint venture.
</P>
<P>
Ju said the new series of Benz buses, offered in models ranging
from 8-12 meters in length, will not only feature more dynamic
generating power and lower fuel consumption, but also be
offered at market prices competitive with domestic models.
</P>
<P>
The corporation has already received orders of 200 units,
according to Ju.
</P>
<P>
The Jiangsu Yaxing Group, the largest bus manufacturer in
China, and Mercedes-Benz, a motor vehicle manufacturing giant in
Germany, established Yaxing-Benz Ltd at a cost of 100 million
U.S. dollars. The joint venture has a designed annual production
capacity of 7,000 buses and 12,000 chassis.
</P>
<P>
Ju pointed out that China's massive investment of 500 billion
yuan for highway construction over the next three years has
created bright prospects for luxury buses.  
