<HEADLINE> Beijingers Learn Dietary Habits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Residents in the Chinese capital
will be encouraged to foster a good dietary habits in order to
ward-off chronic diseases.
</P>
<P>
The goal of a new three-year program centers on emphasizing the
importance of good health, the prevention of diseases and balanced
diets.
</P>
<P>
The number of local residents suffering from high blood
pressure, diabetes, cardiovascular diseases and cancer has been on
the rise in recent years as a result of improved living standards
and the increased intake of meat and fats.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that heart disease, cerebral diseases and
malignant tumors are the leading three "killer diseases" in
Beijing, with the death toll from related diseases standing at
over 66 percent of the local total.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Zonghan, director of the Beijing Municipal Health Bureau,
said that poor dietary habits, smoking, alcohol consumption and
the lack of exercise have accounted for 45 percent of the factors
causing related diseases.
</P>
<P>
The program will include the compilation of reading materials
on diets and organizing health lectures and competitive
activities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
