<HEADLINE> Gansu Records Efficient Use of Overseas Assistance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
is seeking over 50 overseas assitance projects involving over 100
million U.S. dollars by end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The 44 international aid projects in place by April this year
involved contracted investments of 16 million US dollars,
according to the Gansu Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
Department.
</P>
<P>
Major assistance programs include a social development project
in impoverished areas, a UNICEF program which encourages women to
participate in development, a desert reclamation project and a
sustainable rural development project funded by the UNDP, as well
as the Gansu Sprinkler Irrigation Training Center Project and a
dairy project funded by the European Union.
</P>
<P>
Dry farming and rainwater irrigation projects funded by
the UNDP have helped expand applications of agrotechnology, improve
agricultural mechanization and provide drinking water.
</P>
<P>
The UNICEF project has benefitted some 1,684 women in nine
townships. The female farmers have used small loans to establish
various types of profitable businesses. The organization has
granted related loans totalling 2.23 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Gansu has implemented 260 overseas assistance projects
involving over 150 million U.S. dollars by the end of last
year. 
</P>
