the New South Wales state government announced the clean-up a year
ago and committed about 13 million U.S. dollars to the job, it
had not yet issued a tender for the work.
</P>
<P>
Ports Minister Kim Yeadon said the project was progressing
well, with the first phase of site investigation and assessment
almost complete.
</P>
