<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Winter-Spring Rice Crops Do Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 19 (xinhua) -- Vietnam has harvested more than
13.51 million tons of rice from the winter-spring crop, 200,000
tons more than last year, the English-language Vietnam News
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The bumper winter-spring crop has helped lower rice prices and
an estimated 2.8 million tons of rice has been exported over the
past six months, the newspaper quoted the General Department of
Statistics as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, the yield of subsidiary crops was about 1.32 million
tons of rice equivalent, lower than previous years. Maize, the
second staple crop after rice, yielded more than 800,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The department said that the output of the subsidiary crops was
low because many farmers have turned to more profitable sugarcane
and peanuts. As a result, the area sown with maize fell by 3
percent and sweet potato by 3.5 percent compared with last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
