<HEADLINE> Guangdong Set to Implement New Credit Asset Classification System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province has paved
the way for the introduction of an internationally recognized
credit asset classification system for its banking sector.
</P>
<P>
In early May, the People's Bank of China, the nation's central
bank, announced Guangdong would conduct experiments with a
five-level credit asset classification system designed to improve
bank loan management.
</P>
<P>
This system, which classified the quality of loans into five
levels -- current, special mention, substandard, questionable and
losses, will be introduced to banks across the country in August.
</P>
<P>
Some 15,000 banking personnel attended the over 140 training
classes Guangdong banks organized through June 10.
</P>
<P>
"This has prepared the province to enter the implementation
period for the classification system," according to a local
banking official.  
