<HEADLINE> Sino-US Law School Exchanges Proceed Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Sino-US law school exchanges have
developed smoothly and produced remarkable results since the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The conclusion was reached during the seminar on law school
education attended by presidents of more than 30 Chinese and
American law schools and well known legal experts. The seminar
closes today.
</P>
<P>
Participants attended the event as part of exchanges organized
by the Sino-US Legal Education Exchange Committee, universities in
the two countries and the Fullbright Scholars Program of the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Statistics covering the period between 1983-1995 show that
Chinese law schools sent 218 students to study in American law
schools. Over 600 Chinese scholars have attended nine summer
courses on American law organized by the Sino-US Legal Education
Exchange Committee since 1985.
</P>
<P>
Chinese and American universities have organized seminars
covering law education, laws governing the market economy, and the
market economy and legal construction.  
</P>
