<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang Has 25 Open Ports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 19 (Xinhua) --Northeast China's Heilongjiang
Province has 25 open ports offering improved infrastructure,
including advanced telecommunications, ample berths and entrepot
trade, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang borders on the far east region of Russia across
the Amur River or Heilongjiang River in Chinese. The province
shares over 3,000 km of border with Russia.
</P>
<P>
The province's open ports have handled 16 million tons of
foreign trade commodities and completed entry and exit procedures
for more than five million people since 1986.
</P>
<P>
The ports serve as the window for opening and have greatly
promoted friendly exchanges and both economic and trade
cooperation between China and Russia, members of the Commonwealth
of the Independent States (CIS) and numerous other foreign
countries. 
</P>
