<HEADLINE> Circular Urges Increased Pig Purchases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The central government recently
issued a circular urging State-operated marketing enterprises to
expand their purchases of pigs in order to protect the enthusiasm
of pig raisers.
</P>
<P>
The circular was issued in response to the expanding oversupply
of pigs which has already sparked falling prices and marketing
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The State Internal Trade Bureau circular urged all State-owned
food processing enterprises to purchase all pigs offered by
breeders and banned random reductions in purchase prices.
</P>
<P>
The circular also called for enhanced efforts to expand
marketing sources and increased exports.
</P>
<P>
Slaughter houses were urged to further expand the scale of
production. 
</P>
