<HEADLINE> Quake Hits Northern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 19 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.4 on the
open-ended Richter scale jolted the southern part of Japan's
northernmost island Hokkaido on Friday morning, the Meteorological
Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damages or casualties and no
tidal waves warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The center of the quake, which occurred around 11:20 a.m. local
time (0220 GMT), was about 30 kilometers under the Pacific Ocean
off Urakawa on the southern coast of Hokkaido, the agency said.
</P>
