<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Exports Earns 730 million U.S. Dollars From EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam earned 730 million
U.S. dollars from exports to the European Union (EU) in the first
five months of this year, Vietnam News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Garment and textiles led Vietnam's export items to the EU,
fetching 180 million dollars or 40 percent of the country's export
turnover in the past five months.
</P>
<P>
The EU market has also opened for processed aquatic products
from 28 Vietnamese processing enterprises which earned a combined
turnover of 40 million dollars or 13 percent of the sector's total
export turnover.
</P>
<P>
Rice was another export item to European countries with 148,000
tonnes shipped to the Netherlands, 57,000 tonnes to Sweden and
4,000 tonnes to France in the period.
</P>
<P>
The promotion of exports to the EU is a drastic measure that is
helping Vietnamese export enterprises overcome outlet
restrictions. Vietnam's exports to Asian countries, Japan in
particular, have declined due to the on-going regional economic
crisis.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to West European countries early April this
year, Vietnam's Prime Minister Phan Van Khai proposed his hosts to
help Vietnamese goods enter the EU market. The businessmen
accompanying the prime minister met with their EU counterparts to
seek markets for their products.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's imports from the EU stood over 400 million dollars in
the first five months of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
