<HEADLINE> U.S. Urges Kosovo's Albanian Rebels Restrain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The United States urged on
Thursday the Albanians separatists in Kosovo to restrain,
otherwise, conditions in the Serbian province will deteriorate
further.
</P>
<P>
If the ethnic Albanian rebels launch new offensive against
Serbs, it is "a sure-fire way" to give Belgrade another pretext to
kill innocent Albanians, State Department spokesman James Rubin
said at a briefing.
</P>
<P>
"It will not improve the situation. The goal now should be to
reduce violence on both sides," added Rubin.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Rubin criticized Belgrade's refusal to pull its
security forces from the province and to accept direct
international involvement in a dialogue with Albanian
representatives.
</P>
<P>
He noted those steps were demanded by the "contact group" of
nations that has been seeking peace in the province.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that those were critical conditions that needed to
be met for a serious dialogue that had the prospect of succeeding,"
Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has indicated that it will not support an independent
the Albanian-dominated province. 
</P>
