<HEADLINE> Clinton Declares Disaster in Northern Florida Counties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton on
Thursday declared a disaster in eight Floridan counties, where a
wildfire has scorched about 2850 hectares.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which began threatening the town of Waldo Tuesday
night, has forced many of the town's more than 1,000 residents
from their homes.
</P>
<P>
As firefighters battled flames throughout north Florida, the
president's declaration enabled an emergency federal aid to the
eight counties.
</P>
<P>
At least 107 fires have erupted in 28 of Florida's 67 counties
since May 25, burning more than 1800 hectares, causing at least 13
injuries and one death, and damaging more than 80 homes.
</P>
<P>
The lack of rain and record-high temperatures have left many
parts of the state dangerously dry. 
</P>
