<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents Kill 14,000 Thais in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 19 (Xinhua) -- An average 1.57 people died each
hour in traffic accidents in Thailand during the past year, a
local newspaper Friday quoted the Land Transport Department as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Tong Hua Daily News, a local Chinese-language newspaper,
reported that a total of 13,836 people were killed in 82,336
traffic accidents last year, causing 1.57 billion baht (392.8
million U.S. dollars) in property damages.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some 48,700 people were injured in traffic accidents
last year.
</P>
<P>
The department said traffic accident has become the biggest
killer of young people in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
It warned that if the situation continues to worsen, the
numbers of deaths and property damages may double in the next
year.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Health's statistics showed that half of
the accidents were caused by drunken driving. 
</P>
