<HEADLINE> Russia Endorses Federal Budget Saving Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Russian government has ratified
a program aimed at saving 42 billion rubles (about 6.9 billion
U.S. dollars) in expenditure, Finance Minister Mikhal Zadornov
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, the number of institutions receiving money
directly from the federal budget will be reduced and subsidies to
businesses in the red and to residents terminated, Zadornov told a
press conference.
</P>
<P>
The program will also impose fuels and electricity quotas on
institutions that receive state funding.
</P>
<P>
Zadornov said there will be a 20 percent cut in the workforce
of the state-owned enterprises and institutions.
</P>
<P>
The Russian budget this year will have a deficit of tens of
billions of rubles thanks to economic recession, sagging exports
and tax revenues, as well as rising domestic and foreign debts.
</P>
</TEXT>
