<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investment climbed
sharply in the Shenzhen Special Economic Zone in the first five
months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures show that the city neighboring Hong Kong
approved 853 projects involving overseas financing between January
and May, a year-on-year rise of 36.26 percent, with a pledged
investment of 948 million U.S. dollars, up 45.86 percent.
</P>
<P>
The special economic zone utilized 960 million U.S. dollars of
overseas investment in the first five months of this year.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months, 609 projects involving direct
overseas investment were approved, an increase of 93.33 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the period, over 140 overseas-funded enterprises pledged
to expand investment, six of which increase investment by five
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Another upbeat sign is the fact that high-technology projects
make up 45.5 percent of the newly approved projects.
</P>
<P>
The projects solely invested by foreigners and the investment
from Hong Kong and Taiwan make up the bulk of the new overseas
investment.  
