first five months of 1998 registered a 2.16 percent increase over
the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Supermarkets Association announced that the
sector expects the value of the supermarkets sales to have a
growth of 2.5 percent over 1997.
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Brazil will increase its exports of cigarettes
because of the drop in domestic consumption, as forecast by the
Brazilian Smoking Industry Association (Abif).
</P>
<P>
The Abif announced that the domestic use of tobacco in Brazil
dropped from 119 billion cigarettes in 1996 to 110.8 billion in
1997, which caused the growth of exports from 63 billion
cigarettes in 1996 to 72 billion in 1997.
</P>
