SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- The Center of Exhibitions of Colombia,
located in the center of Caracas, the Venezuelan capital, will be
inaugurated on July 8.
</P>
<P>
Colombian goods, like textiles, leather, clothing, food will be
exhibited in the center, and business deals can be made to
promote the bilateral commerce.
</P>
<P>
Colombian President Ernesto Samper will attend the inauguration
of the center.
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Costa Rican exports will amount to about 80
million U.S. dollars in 1998, a 15 percent increase over last year,
Costa Rican Ambassador in Mexico Gonzalo Facio, predicted. 
