<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dominica Hopes to Import Oil from Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Dominica is expected to request
30,000 barrels of oil supply a day from Venezuela as Prime
Minister Edison James pays a two-day official visit to this South
American nation that starts Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This will be James' first trip to Venezuela since he came into
office in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Dominica, one of the east Caribbean islands that won
independence from Britain in 1978, has to import oil worth 6
million U.S. dollars a year.
</P>
<P>
Having only a population of 70,000, Dominica is not an
attractive market for Venezuelan oil, but Caracas believes it is
important to maintain the Venezuelan energy presence in the
east Caribbean islands for diplomatic reasons.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela and Dominica started diplomatic relations in 1979, by
the end of which the two nations signed an agreement of friendship
and cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
