<HEADLINE> Entrepreneurs to Join FTAA Trade Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Entrepreneurial Network of
Hemispheric Integration (REIH) will participate in talks for the
creation of the Free Trade Area for the Americas (FTAA), it was
announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
REIH president and chairman of the Costa Rican Chamber of
Industries Marco Vinicio Ruiz said the entrepreneurs have
committed themselves to present their points of view to their
governments about FTAA talks.
</P>
<P>
It was agreed at REIH's meeting last week in Miami, United
States, that the industrial, services, and agriculture sectors
would deliberate carefully over the topics discussed during the
talks.
</P>
<P>
The FTAA negotiations were launched last April in Santiago,
Chile.
</P>
<P>
The first meeting of the trade negotiation committee for
creation of the FTAA began in Buenos Aires on Wednesday. Delegates
from 34 nations on the South American continent attended the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Although the negotiations to create the FTAA is a task of
governments, the entrepreneurs want to assert their influence in
the process to assure an integration adequate to benefit their
interests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
