<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floods In East, Central China Kill 63 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Torrential rains have engulfed
houses, livestock and cultivated lands in Hunan, Jiangxi and
Fujian provinces, killing 63 people and leaving millions of people
trapped in flooded areas since last week, today's China Daily
reports.
</P>
<P>
In Hunan Province, floods wrecked 26,800 houses, leaving
253,000 residents homeless. Forty people died and more 17,000
people were injured.
</P>
<P>
The flood also killed 32,000 head of livestock and devastated
14,600 hectares of crops.
</P>
<P>
More than five million people, including People's Liberation
Army troops, are involved in the fight against the rising waters.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rainstorms have swelled major rivers over the
warning level in Jiangxi Province, endangering more than four
million residents.
</P>
<P>
The flood destroyed 43,000 houses, killed eight people and
caused injuries or illness to 4,482 people.
</P>
<P>
More than 272,000 hectares of crops were damaged and 15,700
hectares of cultivated land ruined. A total of 6,700 head of
livestock drowned.
</P>
<P>
In Fujian Province, rains triggered floods and landslides,
killing 15 people and injuring another 3,700.
</P>
<P>
Direct economic losses in the three provinces are estimated to
exceed six billion yuan (722 million US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
