<HEADLINE> China's Largest Lubricant Producer Set up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Great Wall Lubricating Oil Group
Co., the largest lubricant producer in China, was set up here
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The group was formed by the merger of China Petrochemical
Corp's Great Wall Premium-grade Lube Oil Co. (GWPLOC) and Yanshan
Lubricants Co. (YLC) and other enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the lubricant group is a strategic
measure to make full use of domestic firms' combined strengths in
confronting fierce competition from foreign firms, said today's
China Daily.
</P>
<P>
To achieve large-scale benefits, the lubricants group merged
Beijing Jingjin Oil Plant and has a majority stake in Shenyang Teli
Lubricant Co. It also signed a letter of intent with Jinling
Petrochemical Corp's No.1 Chemical Factory to hold majority
ownership in the lubricant plant there.
</P>
<P>
It also plans to float shares on the domestic stock market,
said the Beijing-based newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Foreign brands have nibbled at the juicy lubricant oil pie
since China opened its market in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Currently, about 20 percent of domestic market belongs to
foreign competitors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
