<HEADLINE> New Joint Auto Venture Set up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A new joint company,
Herberts-Akzo-Red Lion Automotive Coatings Co. Ltd., was launched
yesterday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
According to Today's China Daily, the move is expected to
strengthen China's fledgling vehicle sector.
</P>
<P>
The new firm was formed on the basis of an old firm, Akzo Red
Lion Automotive Coatings, which has been in existence since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Herberts, coating experts within the Hoechst Group, acquired 51
percent of total shares, while the previous shareholders, Akzo
Nobel coatings of the Netherlands holds 25 percent and Beijing
Red Lion Coatings Co, 24 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-German-Dutch joint venture is capable of providing
high-quality coatings for China's auto producers.
</P>
<P>
Its annual turnover is expected to reach 11.1 million US
dollars in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese partner, Beijing Red Lion Coatings Co, is the
largest automotive coatings producer in the country. Currently,
its products share one quarter of China's total market.
</P>
<P>
With the rapid development of China's auto industry, the demand
for high quality coatings has become huge, resulting in more
foreign cooperation in this field, said the paper. 
</P>
