<HEADLINE> Graf knocked out at Eastbourne Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Steffi Graf of Germany
was knocked out by Russian teenager Anna Kournikova in a
quarter-final match of the women's grass-court tournament in
Eastbourne on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Graf was beaten 6-7 (4-7), 6-3, 6-4 in the 450,000 U.S. dollars
event by 17-year-old Kournikova, 6th seed of the tourney.
</P>
<P>
Kournikova hurt her hand in a fall during the third set and was
taken to hospital straight after the match for an examination.
</P>
<P>
The Russian is due to meet either Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of
Spain or 16-year-old American Serena Williams in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
In another quarter-final match, Natasha Zvereva of Belarus
overwhelmed Magui Serna of Spain 7-6 (7-5), 6-2. 
