<HEADLINE> Beijing Sells Apartments Worth 3 Billion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics show that in
the first five months of this year nearly 3 billion yuan worth of
housing was sold in China's capital.
</P>
<P>
The figure represents a 100 percent increase from the same
period in 1997. .
</P>
<P>
In the January-May period, 620,000 square meters of housing was
sold, according to the Municipal Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Of the total sales volume, 2.36 billion yuan or 80 percent of
the total was residential.
</P>
<P>
The construction of apartment buildings also continued to grow
rapidly. During the five-month period, construction began on 40
million square meters of housing and 1.22 million square meters
was completed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
