<HEADLINE> Chinese Maritime Police Smash Cigarette Smuggling Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Marine police in Ningbo, east
China's Zhejiang Province, have cracked a smuggling case involving
the confiscation of more than 4,000 cases of cigarettes and the
arrest of 17 suspects.
</P>
<P>
The confiscated cigarettes were valued at close to 10 million
yuan (1.2 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
