<DOCNO> XIE19980619.0286 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Meets Jospin Over Asian Crisis, Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton met
French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin Thursday over subjects ranging
from Asia's financial crisis to the Kosovo conflict to strengthen
the often turbulent U.S.-French relationship.
</P>
<P>
Clinton and Jospin had a working lunch at the White House.
Jospin stressed his desire for cordial dealings with Washington.
</P>
<P>
"We had a good visit. We had a lot of areas of agreement,"
Clinton told reporters after the lunch.
</P>
<P>
Jospin told reporters that he and Clinton "share the same
analysis" on Kosovo and that the two countries would continue to
cooperate through the six-nation Contact Group on the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed Asian's financial crisis and the joint
foreign exchange intervention by the United States and Japan to
prop up the yen Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the United States decided to waive U.S. sanctions
that would have prevented French, Russian and Malaysian firms from
carrying out a 2 billion U.S. dollar gas deal in Iran.
</P>
<P>
Jospin said they did not directly discuss U.S. sanctions
policy, but added that Washington and Paris continued to disagree
on the issue. "The positions remain a little different," he said.
</P>
<P>
France has long deplored U.S. sanctions, arguing Washington had
no business imposing its will on commercial transactions between
foreign companies. The overall U.S. sanctions policy is now under
review in Washington.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to the U.S, Jospin is expected to sign a civil
aviation agreement that will free up passenger and cargo traffic
between the two countries after a five-year period of controlled
growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980619.0287 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
