<DOCNO> XIE19980619.0290 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Allows Cuban Planes Fly to Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The United States said Thursday
that it has agreed to allow Cuba's national airline to fly over
U.S. territory on its flights to Canada.
</P>
<P>
The State Department said that the authorization was negotiated
through the International Civil Aviation Organization in Montreal,
where Cuba had lodged a complaint that the U.S. ban violated
international overflight rules.
</P>
<P>
The United States has agreed to authorize Cubana airlines to
use two specified Cuba-Canada overland routes and to provide
normal air navigation services, said the State Department.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban air authorities have complained that Cuba's airplane
has had to make costly detours over the Atlantic on daily flights
to Montreal and Toronto While U.S. carriers flying to South
America from Miami fly over Cuba. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
