<HEADLINE> France Qualify with 4-0 Win over Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-DENIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- France beat Saudi Arabia 4-0 to
qualify for the top 16 but playmaker Zinedine Zidane got a red card
and will miss the next match.
</P>
<P>
The host team dominated the match, especially after the 18th
minute when Mohammed Al Khilaiwi of Saudi Arabia was sent off for a
dangerous tackle.
</P>
<P>
But the host team failed to score until the 36th minute when
Thierry Henry tab in a cross from Laurent Blanc.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi Arabian team played hard in the second half though
they had one man less. That gave the French team more rooms for
attack and French substitute David Trezeguet slamed home a loose
ball to put the hosts 2-0 ahead.
</P>
<P>
At the 25th minute, French midfielder and playmaker Zidane was
also sent off for rough play. The Saudi Arabians went all out,
trying to get a goal back.
</P>
<P>
But they suffered another blow at the 77th minute when French
goalie Fabien Barthez launched a fast counter-attack and Henry beat
the Saudi Arabian defenders with an easy shot.
</P>
<P>
Blanc hommered home another goal at the 85th minute to seal the
victory for the French team.
</P>
<P>
The win ensured the host team a berth in the top 16 no matter
what the result is in their final group match against Denmark.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Thursday, Denmark were forced to a 1-1 draw by South
Africa. They need at least a draw against France to salvage the
other qualifying slot from the group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
