<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Reconstruction, Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank okayed two loans
totaling 76.9 million U.S. dollars equivalent to finance
reconstruction and infrastructure projects in Croatia.
</P>
<P>
The first loan of some 40.6 million dollars will be provided
for the country's reconstruction project for Eastern Slavonia,
Baranja and Western Srijem. This project will repair and rebuild
war-damaged water sector infrastructure, critically needed to
restart the local economy of these regions, while mitigating the
negative environmental impact to be caused to the adjacent nature
park by the restart of local agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The second loan of 36.3 million dollars equivalent will be
utilized for the Croatia municipal environmental infrastructure
project. This project will reduce municipal wastewater pollutant
discharges into the environmentally sensitive Kastela and Trogir
Bays consistent with Croatian and European Union stands, and
improve the safety, reliability and delivery of drinking water in
the project area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
