<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Assists Guinea-Bissau Water, Energy Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Thursday an interest-free credit of some 20.25 million U.S.
dollars equivalent for the Guinea-Bissau water and energy project.
</P>
<P>
This project will alleviate the effects of poverty and improve
health by increasing access to safe and affordable water and
sanitation, ensure reliable and affordable supply of water and
electricity for economic growth, improve water pricing and
electricity tariffs for cost recovery and develop the government's
regulatory and planning capacity in these areas.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association, the World Bank's concessional lending
wing for developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
