<HEADLINE> Turkish Prime Minister Visits Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Political ties between Romania
and Turkey are "excellent," said the prime ministers of the two
countries, Radu Vasile and Mesut Yilmaz, Thursday after their
first round of talks.
</P>
<P>
Romanian Prime Minister Radu Vasile said that biennial mutual
visits would take place, to which short visits would be added
whenever needed. He said that bilateral economic ties were
potential between the two countries and necessary means had been
established in order to overstep the ceiling of 1 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Radu Vasile said the two sides were ready to support investment
projects in the energy, transports, oil and machine-building
fields.
</P>
<P>
In his turn, Mesut Yilmaz said the visit to Bucharest was an
opportunity to strengthen cooperation between the two countries.
He added that a free trade agreement between Romania and Turkey
that came into force in February 1998 made a contribution to the
development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Mesut Yilmaz arrived in Bucharest Thursday morning on a two-day
official visit. He is the first prime minister of Turkey who
visits Romania after a 12-year break-off. Mesut Yilmaz is
accompanied by many businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is a very important partner of Romania not only in the
political aspect, but also in the economic domain. The volume of
bilateral trade was 567 million U.S. dollars in 1997, and is
expected to reach 1 billion this year. Turkey is at the same time
among the most important investors in Romania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
