<HEADLINE> Vogts Praises Veteran Matthaus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- German coach Berti Vogts praised
veteran Lothar Matthaeus who didn't played a single minute in
Germany's first match against the United States."
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held at Saint Paul de Vence, Vogts
said:"Matthaus has a very positive attitude towards the rest of the
team."
</P>
<P>
"We are trying to learn some lessons from our match against the
United States in order to improve our organisation." said Vogts.
</P>
<P>
"I am particularly happy to have a player in our ranks with the
clout of Lothar Matthaus. He has a very positive attitude towards
the rest of the team," said Vogts, "He trains very hard and is a
good example to the others." 
</P>
