<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria, Bulgaria to Play Crucial Match at Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Super Eagles Nigeria and last World
Cup semi-finalists Bulgaria will play a crucial group match at Parc
des Princes Stadium on Friday.
</P>
<P>
To the Nigerians, they will be fresh in their minds with the
memorable 3-2 victory over Spain as they prepare for the clash with
Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
As to the Bulgarians, the Paris stadium holds great memories for
striker Emil Kostadinov who scored a last-gasp winner to shatter
France's qualifying hopes for the World Cup finals in the United
States four years ago.
</P>
<P>
"That memory will be with me all my life," said Kostadinov, "I
hope that Friday brings me and Bulgaria even more happiness."
</P>
<P>
The two teams are familiar with each other as four years ago at
Dallas, Nigeria trounced Bulgaria 3-0 in the group stage with Daniel
Amokachi netting twice.
</P>
<P>
Amokachi is expected to get a berth in the starting line-up as
he has recovered from an injured knee which ruled him out of the
Nigeria-Spain match.
</P>
<P>
Another Nigerian star Nwanko Kanu, who plays for Italian club
Inter Milan, is also available following a stomach complaint.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria will be without midfielder Anatoli Nankov who got the
first red card of this World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian coach Hristo Bonev warned his team:"To beat the
Nigerians, we have to be very disciplined, very concentrated and
every player has to be at their best." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
