<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain Can Afford No More Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-ETIENNE, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Spain can afford no more defeat
when they meet Paraguay in their second group match here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 3-2 loss at the hands of Super Eagles Nigeria has been a major
blow to the Spaniards, who are second in the FIFA rankings behind
Brazil and have been regarded by many as one of the favorites of the
World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Spanish media has piled blames on coach Javier Clemente and
goal-keeper Andoni Zubizarreta after the shock defeat.
</P>
<P>
Clemente was slammed for fielding a team without a real striker
while Zubizarreta was blamed for letting in three goals in just one
match.
</P>
<P>
Clemente will have to make changes to his starting line-up but
he insisted that Zubzarreta would contiune in goal.
</P>
<P>
"We were jolted by the defeat but we've had a few days to
collect ourselves," said Clemente, "We didn't play so badly really
and if we win our two remaining matches we are through."
</P>
<P>
Paraguay, who forced Bulgaria to a 0-0 draw, will be in full
strength as tough defender Francisco Arce and striker Miguel Angel
Benitez have recovered from injuries they sustained in the first
match.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay's Brazilian coach Paulo Cesar Carpegiani pinpointed
Arce as their key man in the match against the Spaniards,"Arce is
fundamental to our plan as he breaks things up and holds the line
superbly." said Carpegiani.
</P>
<P>
But the Paraguay goal-keeper Jose Luis Chilavert, a penalty and
free-kick expert, would as usual took the limelight of the match.
</P>
</TEXT>
