<HEADLINE> World Cup Internet Site Receives 18 Million Hits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS. June 18 (Xinhua) -- International soccer governing body FIFA
said here on Thursday that the official World Cup website on the
Internet has received millions of hits so far.
</P>
<P>
The site (www.france98.com) became one of hottest sports website by
recording 18 million hits so far, said FIFA spokesman Kaith Cooper.
</P>
<P>
The number has exceeded that registered by the website set up by
the organizers of the Olympic Games in 1996, Cooper said. 
