<HEADLINE> Colombian Coach to Quit after World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- After kicking out star striker
Faustino Asprilla, Colombian coach Hernan Dario Gomez announced on
Thursday that he was quitting at the end of the World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Gomez has been angered over persistent rumors that a foreign
coach was being lined up to replace him.
</P>
<P>
Bora Milutinovic and Brazilan paulo Cesar Carpeggiani have both
been named as possible replacements.
</P>
<P>
Gomez said:"If certain officials think they can get someone
better so be it. I am on my way out, my period in charge is coming
to a close."
</P>
<P>
Gomez, 41, denied that his decision was connected to the
Asprilla affair.
</P>
<P>
Gomez was assistant coach four years ago at the United States
World Cup finals. He took the Colombian team to the third place in
the South American qualifers behind Argentina and Paraguay to reach
the World Cup finals. 
</P>
