<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> McCarthy Saves South Africa from Elimination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOULOUSE, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Benedict McCarthy scored a
second-half equalizer against Danmark here on Thursday to keep South
Africa's hope for the last 16 alive in the soccer World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Three players were sent off in the Group C contest held between the
former European champion and the African upstart in Municipal Stadium
here.
</P>
<P>
After trailing Denmark 1-0, Ajax Amsterdam striker McCarthy slotted
the ball home from in the box seven minutes into the second half after
some dazzling short passes.
</P>
<P>
John Moshoeu tapped the ball toward striker Shaun Bartlett, who
chipped it to 21-year-old McCarthy to score.
</P>
<P>
Allen Nielsen gave Denmark a 1-0 lead by netting on a Brian Laudrup
pass from right in the 12th minute.
</P>
<P>
Denmark, who dominated the first half, almost made it 2-0 in the
40th minute had a blast from Ebbe Sand not hit the right-hand post.
</P>
<P>
The Bafana Bafana boys rallied strongly after break, melting the
Danish defence which had been impenetrable in the first half.
</P>
<P>
Referee John Toro Rendon flashed two red cards within three minutes
from 67th to 69th minutes, dispatching Denmark's Miklos Molnar first
and then South African Alfred Phiri.
</P>
<P>
The Danes were further reduced to 9 men after substitute Morten
Wieghorst was given the marching order in the 40th minute, only his
third minutes on pitch.
</P>
<P>
Quinton Fortune almost clinched a victory for South Africa in
injury time when his 30-meter shot hit the crossbar.
</P>
<P>
Besides the red cards, the seven yellow cards, four to South Africa
and three to Denmark, also made record in the competition so far, 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
