<HEADLINE> South Africa Coach Says Squad Improved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOULOUSE, June 18 (Xinhua) -- South Africa head coach Philippe
Troussier said after their 1-1 draw with Denmark that his team had
improved a lot since their loss against France.
</P>
<P>
Troussier said, "Compared to our first game against France, we
played with more space. The beginning was terrible but in the second
half we were more threatening and even outlasted them physically."
</P>
<P>
"With a lot of lessons learned and improved rhythm, we had thought
we could play to a higher level today, although we faced a more
experienced Danish team," the Frenchman said.
</P>
<P>
Troussier added, "Today we played more compactly, especially in
defence. We focused more on counter-attacks and consequently were
weaker in the front." 
</P>
</TEXT>
