<HEADLINE> Denmark Coach Ponders Unpredicability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOULOUSE, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Denmark coach Bo Johansson pondered
the unpredicability of the sport of soccer after Thursday's 1-1 draw
with South Africa here.
</P>
<P>
"Soccer is like this. You play well for some periods of the match
and then incredibly bad periods," he said.
</P>
<P>
"It is both joy and tears," he added.
</P>
<P>
But Johansson declined to comment the refereeing of the game, which
saw two Danes and one South African sent off.
</P>
<P>
Danish substitutes Mikos Molnar and Morten Wieghorst was given the
marching order in the second half, the first time that Denmark had two
red cards in a game.
</P>
<P>
"It is better that I don't say anything at all," he said. 
</P>
