<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Red-carded Substitutes Make History </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOULOUSE, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The 1-1 draw between South Africa and
Denmark on Thursday was the first game in the history of the World Cup
finals in which three substitutes were sent off.
</P>
<P>
Danes Morten Wieghorst and Miklos Molnar and South Africa's Alfred
Phiri were given the marching orders by Colombian referee John Tairo
Toro Rendo.
</P>
<P>
Only two previous World Cup games, in 1938 and 1954, had seen three
players sent off but it is the first time that three substitutes were
sent off. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
