<HEADLINE> IMF Delays Loan Disbursement to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary Fund
(IMF) Thursday delayed the repayment of a 670 million U.S. dollar
loan to Russia for a week.
</P>
<P>
An IMF spokesman issued a brief statement announcing the delay
of the executive board's expected action on the latest installment
from a 9.2 billion dollar three-year support loan to Russia.
</P>
<P>
The IMF wants Russia to assure that broad tax code revisions
will become law. Other actions include passing stalled land-reform
and budget laws as well as various tax increases, including a
boost in sales taxes.
</P>
<P>
The IMF said earlier that its No. 2 official, Stanley Fischer,
would visit Moscow next week for talks with top officials on
economic reform and actions on an expanded aid program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
